message.content: The likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are "cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CC". This is because the paper deals with question classification using a BERT-based model, which falls under the domains of natural language processing (NLP), machine learning (ML), and information retrieval (IR). Specifically, the paper focuses on science exam questions, which can be classified as a sub-domain of NLP. The use of a hierarchical taxonomy for classification also suggests a focus on ML techniques. Finally, the paper's emphasis on improving question answering systems aligns with the domain of IR.
